'''Jason W.A. Tucker''' was the Supervising Editor of the ''[[Star Wars: The Clone Wars]]'' animated series and the [[Star Wars: The Clone Wars (film)|theatrical film]] that preceded it. Tucker is currently still at [[Lucasfilm Animation]].

Graduating from [[Wikipedia:Emerson College|Emerson College]] in [[1990]] with a B.F.A in Mass Communication/Film, Tucker started out as an Apprentice Editor at Universal Pictures, working up to Trailer Editor (mostly editing International Trailers and TV Spots). Soon after he moved onto one-hour dramas, working as an Assistant Editor on [[Wikipedia:Sleepwalkers (TV_series)|''Sleepwalkers'']], ''Buddy Faro'', ''Party of Five'', and ''MYOB'', eventually landing feature work as the First Assistant Editor on the [[Warner Bros.]] film [[Wikipedia:Cats & Dogs|''Cats & Dogs'']], as well as the Polish Brothers film, [[Wikipedia:Northfork|''Northfork'']].

His first job as an Animation Editor came on Joe Dante's [[Wikipedia:Looney Tunes Back In Action|''Looney Tunes: Back In Action'']], where he worked closely with the Animation Director, [[Wikipedia:Eric Goldberg (film director)|Eric Goldberg]]. Afterward, he went onto edit more projects with Warner Animation and [[The Walt Disney Company|Disney]] Studios, while intermittently working as an Assistant Editor on [[Wikipedia:Boston Public|''Boston Public'']], [[Wikipedia:CSI: Miami|''CSI: Miami'']], and a VFX Assistant Editor on the animated film [[Wikipedia:Monster House (film)|''Monster House'']].

